\v 11 \add but\add* if he¦35481 doesn't provide these¦35479 three¦35477 things to her, then she can go¦35483 free without¦35484 \add ≈having to pay anything\add*.
\s1 Rules about violence to others
\rem /s1 The Law concerning Violence; Laws about Violent Acts; Cases of Personal Injury; Personal Injuries
\p
\v 12 Whoever strikes¦35489 \add #someone\add* and¦35491 \add #that person\add* dies¦35491, must definitely be put to death¦35493.\x + \xo 21:12: \xt Lev 24:17.\x*
\v 13 But if \add ≈it wasn't premeditated\add*—if God¦35498 had let it happen¦35499 as an accident—then I'll assign a place¦35503 where¦35504 \add @the one who hit them\add* can flee to.\x + \xo 21:13: \xt Num 35:10-34; Deu 19:1-13; Josh 20:1-9.\x*
\v 14 \add However,\add* if \add #someone\add* \add ≈had schemed to trap and¦35509\add* kill¦35516 \add #their\add* neighbour¦35515, then \add even if the killer clings to\add* my altar¦35519, you must take¦35520 \add #them\add* for execution.
\p
\v 15 Anyone who strikes¦35524 \add #their\add* father¦35525 or mother¦35526 must certainly be put to death¦35528.
\p
\v 16 Anyone who abducts another person—either to sell or to keep \add as a slave\add*—\add @that person\add* must certainly be put to death¦35536.\x + \xo 21:16: \xt Deu 24:7.\x*
\p
\v 17 Anyone who curses¦35539 \add #their\add* father¦35540 or mother¦35541 must certainly be put to death¦35543.\x + \xo 21:17: \xt Lev 20:9; Mat 15:4; Mrk 7:10.\x*
\p
\v 18 If¦35553 \add #two people\add* fight and \add #one\add* hits \add #their\add* neighbour¦35555 with a stone¦35556 or with \add #their\add* fist, and \add #the injured one\add* doesn't die¦35560 but is bedridden,
\v 19 if \add #that person\add* \add eventually\add* rises and can walk about outside¦35568 using a staff¦35571, then the \add #person who struck¦35573 them\add* is free, other than \add ≈reimbursing the costs of their lost work and their medical expenses\add*.
\p
\v 20 If a \add #master\add* hits \add #their\add* male or female¦35591 slave with a staff and \add @the slave\add* dies, then the death must certainly¦35596 be avenged¦35596.
\v 21 However¦35608, if \add @the slave\add* is able to stand within a couple of days¦35604, then the \add owner\add* won't be \add ≈punished\add* because \add @the slave\add* is \add #their\add* property¦35609.
\p
\v 22 If \add #two people\add* fight together¦35615 and strike a pregnant¦35619 woman and \add ≈cause her to deliver the baby\add*, if there's no serious injury, then he must certainly¦35625 be fined¦35626 whatever the husband¦35630 of the woman \add ≈demands\add* and the judges¦35633 allow.
\v 23 But if there's serious injury, then you must give a life for a life,
\v 24 an eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth, a hand for a hand, a foot for a foot,\x + \xo 21:24: \xt Lev 24:19-20; Deu 19:21; Mat 5:38.\x*
\v 25 a burn for a burn, a wound for a wound, and a bruise for a bruise.
\p
\v 26 If a \add #master\add* hits \add #their\add* male or female¦35681 slave's eye and damages it, \add #they\add* must let \add @the slave\add* go free in compensation for the eye.
